      {
        "content": "SWC-113: DoS with Failed Call / Unexpected Revert\n\nExternal calls can fail accidentally or deliberately, causing a DoS if the calling contract depends on the call succeeding (e.g. paying many recipients in a loop). Remediation: favor pull over push payments; isolate external calls into their own transactions.",
